  <!-- Hero Section with Background Image -->
  <header class="hero-image">
    <div class="hero-overlay">
      <h1 class="display-4 fw-bolder">Caltech Project</h1>
      <p class="lead fw-normal">GC–Orbitrap Site-Specific Isotope Analysis of Phytane</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <!-- Main Content -->
  <section class="py-5">
    <div class="container px-5">
      
      <!-- Intro -->
      <div class="mb-5">
        <h2 class="fw-bolder">Overview</h2>
        <p class="lead">
          At Caltech, we designed a novel gas chromatography–Orbitrap mass spectrometry 
          (GC–Orbitrap) method that enabled the <strong>first direct site-specific carbon isotope 
          analysis of phytane</strong>. This work combined advanced chromatography with high-resolution 
          mass spectrometry to resolve isotope distributions previously inaccessible by IRMS.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Image with purple box -->
      <div class="text-center mb-5">
        <div class="purple-box shadow">
          <img src="assets/project_caltech.jpg" alt="Caltech GC–Orbitrap phytane project">
          <p class="small mt-2">Figure 1. GC–Orbitrap setup for site-specific isotope measurements of phytane.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Methods -->
      <div class="mb-5">
        <h2 class="fw-bolder">Methods</h2>
        <p>
          We developed a gas chromatography separation tailored to phytane and coupled it to 
          a high-resolution Orbitrap analyzer. This approach exploited fragment-specific isotope 
          ratios, allowing us to reconstruct <em>intramolecular δ<sup>13</sup>C patterns</em>. The method 
          was benchmarked against theoretical isotope models and validated using standards.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Results -->
      <div class="mb-5">
        <h2 class="fw-bolder">Key Results</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Demonstrated the first direct site-specific carbon isotope analysis of phytane.</li>
          <li>Revealed position-specific δ<sup>13</sup>C differences across phytane’s carbon skeleton.</li>
          <li>Showed how site-specific isotope data can inform ancient biosynthetic pathways.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Impact -->
      <div class="mb-5">
        <h2 class="fw-bolder">Impact</h2>
        <p>
          This project provided a proof-of-concept for applying GC–Orbitrap workflows in 
          <strong>geobiology and organic geochemistry</strong>. By accessing intramolecular isotope 
          signatures, we open new possibilities for reconstructing early life metabolisms, 
          petroleum origins, and molecular diagenesis processes.
        </p>
      </div>
      
      <!-- Back link -->
      <div class="text-center">
        <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="projects.html">← Back to Projects</a>
      </div>
      
    </div>
  </section>

